- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on privacy-preserving machine learning using homomorphic encryption.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for machine learning tasks.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper addresses the issue of user privacy in machine learning as a service.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of the Paillier cryptosystem for encrypting data.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper presents a new model for machine learning as a service.
